In this dataset there are 10841 observation and 13 variables.

Categories

There are more family applications on google apps than any other category followed by health and fitness apps. There are less than 500 applications for most of the categories on the list.

Installs

Rating

##    Min. 1st Qu.  Median    Mean 3rd Qu.    Max.    NA's 
##   1.000   4.000   4.300   4.192   4.500   5.000    1474

The ratings of the apps on the app store follows a left skewed distribution. most apps are rated above 4.0 and about half are rated between 4.3 and 5.

Genres

Type

There are a lot more free apps in the app store than paid apps. But we need to keep in mind that some of these free apps have in app purchases or they are free to download but not to use.

Content Rating

Most apps are suitable for people under the age of 18, with the apps that have an E rating more than all the other categories combined.

Univariate Analysis

What is the structure of your dataset?

In this dataset there is infortmation about 10841 apps that are available in the google app store and 13 columns.

About some of the columns:

Type - Free or paid

Categories - There are 33 different Categories (once you remove 1.9)

Installs- There are 21 different levels for installs that tell us how many times the app has been installed. The levels are not evenly spaced. (once you remove free)

Rating - The apps can be rated from 1-5

Genres - There are 120 different Genres

Content.Rating - An application can be given 5 different content rating; Teen, Mature 17+, Everyone 10+, Everyone, Adults only 18+. Some of the applications are not rated

The columns in our dataset - Category, Installs, Type, Content.Rating, Genres, current.ver, Android.ver., last.updated, Apps ,Rating, Reviews, size and price.
